    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.66"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">66</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 20, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Robert <hi rend="caps">L.</hi> Pullen, the former registrar of McCook College and now retired, plans to present a gift to the new college library. He wishes for this gift to be a panel of portraits which will include the pictures of yourself, Willa Cather, and Mari Sandoz. The selection is his own, based upon his admiration of these three great Nebraska authors and his life-long interest in Nebraska history. He believes these authors have contributed the most to preserving the history of this state in story, poetry and prose.</p> 
                
                <p>The local photographer will make up the panel of portraits if I can obtain the pictures for him to work with. Do you have a photograph of yourself that I may use for this purpose? An 8x10 picture would be preferred but any size will be appreciated.</p> 
                
                <p>I promise to return the picture to you promptly as soon as the panel is completed. If you have any suggestions or comments concerning Mr. Pullen's intended gift to the McCook College Library, we will appreciate hearing from you.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Mrs. Valois H. Pullen</signed> 
                    <signed>Mrs. Valois H. Pullen</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
